             was indicted for that <rs id="t17950114-36-off212" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17950114-36-off212" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950114-36-off212" type="offenceSubcategory" value="mail"></interp>
               he, on <rs id="t17950114-36-cd213" type="crimeDate">22d of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950114-36-off212 t17950114-36-cd213"></join>, being a person <rs id="t17950114-36-deflabel214" type="occupation">employed in sorting packages and letters</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950114-36-defend302 t17950114-36-deflabel214"></join>, in the parish <placeName id="t17950114-36-crimeloc215">St. Mary Woolnorth, London</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t17950114-36-crimeloc215" type="placeName" value="St. Mary Woolnorth, London"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950114-36-crimeloc215" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950114-36-off212 t17950114-36-crimeloc215"></join>, sent by the post to the general Post office on the same day, a certain letter, lately before sent by one 
                     
                        <persName id="t17950114-36-victim304" type="victimName">
                           Joseph 
                           Robinson
                        <interp inst="t17950114-36-victim304" type="surname" value="Robinson"></interp>
